description: As Wolverine and Archangel battle the Undercloaks, Psylocke's condition takes a turn.
name: Quest for the Crimson Dawn

description:
The origin of Dolphin is revealed as she is put on trial for crimes against an underwater people who have made Aquaman their king.

Aquaman alongside the Queen of Hy-Brasil inspect the vault of weapons with Aquaman being surprised by the vast amount of fire power now under his control.Meanwhile a lonely Dolphin is attacked by mentally causing her to lash out, causing damage to the city and be attacked by several of them. Aquaman then rushes to her aid demanding her to be released but is overturned by the queen who sentences her to death.Meanwhile Atlan watches on at Aquaman's delima while continuing to prepare Garth for his return, following his training.

The queen then decides that the High Seer will look into Dolphin's past, as Admiral Strom continues his flight to meet with someone. The High Seer is then killed when pushing further into Dolphin's mind, but Dolphin is saved due to her actions being pardoned by him before he began. Aquaman and Dolphin then leave in disgust, upon their leaving the Queen is murdered by her subjects who pledge to aid Aquaman when the time arrives. Strom then arrive sin a mountain lair to give advanced warning that Aquaman will likely arrive their, much to the Ocean Master's happiness.
name: Biblical Sense

description:
This is it! Wolverine’s showdown with Genesis of the Clan Akkaba! Luckily for Logan, Cannonball’s not far behind. Will Cyber’s Adamantium restore Wolverine to his former prime?

Story begins with Wolverine and Zoe Culloden arriving to Akkaba a small village in Egypt where the people were massacred by Genesis and a mysterious man called Jamil awaits them to lead Wolverine into a trap. Zoe Culloden having prior commitments leaves Wolverine to meet his fate, Wolverine fully aware of a possible trap forces Jamil to lead him to Apocalypse citadel to face his enemies. Upon arriving he threatens to kill Jamil if he informs Genesis or the Dark Riders of his presence, Jamil leaves Wolverine alone near the Citadel to make his way further in. Cannonball having been chasing trail arrives in Mandripoor and meets up with Tyger Tyger who shows him a Warp Chamber in what remains of LL&L building. Cannonball upon entering arrives in Egypt and follows the foot trail to its source.

Wolverine becomes enraged upon seeing what remains of the Akkaba survivors being taken prisoner meant to be sacrificed in order to resurrect Apocalypse while hiding beneath the sands, Once Wolverine manages to make it into the citadel he is spotted by Dirt Nap

who leads Wolverine into an ambush while he is distracted by Dirt Nap due to Wolverine being angry and wanting back the kid that Dirt Nap had absorbed into himself in a previous story.

Genesis manages to shoot Wolverine with a futuristic weapon knocking Wolverine out and the final scene showing Wolverine floating inside a giant water filled tank and beside another an adamantium skeleton that Genesis hopes to reintroduce into his body.
name: Mythic Of Metal Forged

description: In this penultimate issue, Diablo drags the Force to his personal hell! But what mystery villain is behind the scenes?
name: Agendas Diabolik!

description: Just as the title implies. This is silent issue with images of Cassy and Lusiphur's sex life mixed with images of their assassin hits.
name: Four: Sex and Violence

description: Kahvi rescues a wolf and reveals that she is a Wolfrider by virtue of her father Two-Spear's lineage. Thus are the Go-Backs related.
name: PRIDEFALL

description: In the twilight of his life, Leonardo is attended by an adoring new apprentice, Francesco Melzi, who has replaced the beloved Salai. While conducting an anatomy lesson for the King of France, the failing Maestro performs a dual dissection - one on the flesh, the other on his own life.
Batman learns of the existence of a horrific plague that may be on the brink of spreading to Gotham City.
name: Falls Upon The Apocalypse Plague: Contagion: Part One

description: Guest-starring Captain America! The Enchantress lends a hand to Thor in battle, while the Zodiac’s evil machinations continue to unfold.
name: First Sign, Part 2: Doin' the Zodiac Rag

description:
The Sovereigns have a snowball fight! (Finale thinks the sky is falling)

Meanwhile, Maitresse continues her plan to escape her prison to peruse her escaped daughter, Cascade.
name: 12th Night

description: Superman helps Spectre find the piece of the American Talisman that is located in Metropolis.

An alien scourge threatens to destroy Earth's solar system, but with so many Legionnaires expelled, injured or missing, the remaining heroes stand virtually no chance of stopping the threat...until the United Planets forces them to recruit five of the most powerful beings in the cosmos: the Fatal Five!

To fight an approaching Sun Eater, the Legion learns of a group of meta beings the United Planets had engineered for such a contingency. The Legionnaires must now assemble this difficult group - the Fatal Five.
name: The Gathering Doom

description:
(continued from Detective 695) 
(continued in Catwoman 31)  
Robin and Catwoman teamed up to find the survivor as they plague spread in Gotham City. Batman asked Azrael to follow and watch out for Robin. He and Catwoman found the survivor only to come in second to a man calling himself Tracker. He hit them from behind; Azrael appeared.
name: Contagion, Part 3: Natural Born Healer

description: Tiffany lops off Spawn's head, only to see it turn into a mass of maggots in her hand -- she's been tricked! Spawn attacks, while the evil creatures in the woods gather to aid him. Together, they reduce the angel to bloody scraps. Spawn returns to New York and meets Cog, who warns Spawn that he must gain control of his costume. Meanwhile, Sam shares with Twitch his dream of opening his own detective agency.
name: Warriors

description: Catwoman and Robin have joined togethet to find Dr. Stuart, the only person that survived the Virus, and bring hope to Gotham city.  Azrael arrives to help them on Batman's orders but proves to be almost as much hindrance as help before he figures who is on who's team.
name: Contagion, Part 5: Flesh and Fire

description: Therese Sorenson is dead. Before that, she was what you might call "too smart for her own good" -- smart enough to create a genetic retrovirus that can rewrite living DNA, and smart enough to know that in the wrong hands, her retrovirus could be used as a deadly weapon. In this case, those "wrong hands" belong to Therese's ex-employer, the Biovoc corporation. Rather than let Biovoc get a grip on the retrovirus, Therese and her cloned assistants took their own lives by blowing up their lab. But even that might not have done the trick, since Therese left behind an errant android containing a prototype of the retrovirus. Now it's up to her only surviving clones -- Queenie of the Heartbreakers and former lab assistant Vector -- to carry on their dead boss' kamikaze mission by keeping the retrovirus away from Biovoc. Welcome to the near-future adventures of the Heartbreakers, at long last starring in their own miniseries after making nine appearances in DHP over the last seven years!

A Rage is Arkham Part 1 Spinning out of the Bloodline crossover event, Tommy Monaghan is the only hitman in Gotham City to take on super-powered contracts. Using his x-ray vision and telepathy, Tommy has an upper-hand on the criminal element he removes for a cost. However a new million dollar contract puts Tommy within the sights of another Gotham City vigilante. Thus begins one of the greatest comic runs mixing sincerity, violence, paranormal entities, and lots and lots of bullets from some of the most crazed creators in the medium.

Issue one of the acclaimed series from Garth Ennis and John McCrea.

Tommy Monaghan is a hitman specialising in the elimination of superheroes.

A couple of demons from Hell want to recruit him. And they send one of their lieutenants to do the job.

Also, someone wants him to kill...The Joker?! Yes. Joker.
name: A Rage in Arkham, Part One

description: Emerging from the wreckage of the outside world, Pencil and Nickel at last stand before the symbol of their desperate search--the fabled "Aluminum Tower." But is it really everything that they dreamed of?
name: The Aluminum Tower

description: Last Issue

Overview
It seemed so harmless at first. Concrete was just going to observe a group of Earth First!ers -- to see firsthand what they were all about and to write about their efforts to save an old-growth forest. But that was before the group talked Concrete into illegally entering Canada, and before they decided to "monkey-wrench" some logging equipment, and before the owners of that equipment unexpectedly showed up. Now it's up to Concrete to save them all -- even if it means risking his own life.

Comics' longest-running anthology series serves up another feast of diverse delights, starting with a chunk of "The Ninth Gland" by Renée French, the creator of Fantagraphics's Grit Bath. It's the weird but strangely sweet story about a janitor named Huey Kittentank and two young girls who perform surgery to save the life of an unnamable foundling creature from the girls' back yard. More strange critters inhabit Jack Pollock's latest Devil Chef culinary caper, as the Chef's protégé-gone-wrong carries out unholy gustatory experiments using -- tapeworms! Paul Pope's "The One-Trick Rip Off" continues its gritty excursion into a noir Los Angeles, replete with crime, thievery, and thuggery. Finally, newcomers Scott Gillis and Jeff DeMos offer the black humor of "The Perfect Tree," the story of a suicide attempt that doesn't go quite according to plan. Renée French and Laura Allred (Madman Comics) have created an eerily evocative cover, portraying Huey Kittentank from "The Ninth Gland." DHP #108 is your one-stop shop for all flavors from the sweet to the weird.

Eight years -- that's what it cost Hartigan to save that little girl. Eight years in the pen, and now he's all alone. Not a friend in the world. His wife Eileen didn't stick around, not once he was convicted of raping little Nancy. But Hartigan knows the truth. And Nancy knows the truth. And the handful of other people who know the truth -- the ones who are still alive -- they're the real criminals here. They're the ones who set him up. They're the ones who are gonna settle the eight-year debt. Even it up. Until Nancy and Hartigan are the only ones left who know the truth . . .

Earth is only a distant memory to John Carter, a memory he wants to keep distant. Mars is savage and brutal, but far more honest than the blue planet he left behind. If Carter allows Tarzan to return to his home planet, it could lead to an earthly invasion of Barsoom . . . an invasion which Carter fears his adopted home would be hard pressed to stave off. So, to ensure he never has to see Mars compromised by humans, Carter will see that Tarzan is buried six-feet under its surface.
name: Farewell To Mars

description: The close of sixteenth century Japan is regarded as the Age of Civil Wars, as feudal lords fought amongst themselves for land and power. When one leader finally rose above the others and was proclaimed Shogun, a peace came upon Japan and the samurai warriors found themselves suddenly unemployed. Many of these Ronin turned to banditry to survive, others found work with minor lords. And a small number traveled the musha shugyo -- the warrior pilgrimage -- to hone their spiritual and martial skills. But whether they took the honest road or the crooked path, the Ronin all found one common link -- they were generally less than welcome. Such is the tale of Usagi Yojimbo.
name: Noodles, Part 1

person_credits.name: Stan Sakai
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description:
"Contagion" part 6, continued from AZRAEL (1995-2003) #15. Robin, Nightwing and the Huntress try to suppress rioters as panic over the Clench virus spreads through Gotham City. Meanwhile, Batman's search for a cure leads him to Arkham Asylum! Continued in BATMAN: SHADOW OF THE BAT #49.

Gotham City had been quarantined. Robin delivered the blood to Batman, who began working with it in attempt to create an antidote. Azrael soon arrived with a second blood sample. Nightwing offered his services in the battle. Batman got Poison Ivy out of Arkham so that she (being completely immune to all things) could deliver the antidote to the residents of Babylon Towers. Nightwing and Robin attempted to stop rioters outside the strong hold; Huntress joined them as Ivy entered. The police went to James Gordon for leadership.
name: Contagion, Part 6: Tears of Blood

description:
Tim's father isn't very happy about Tim's new tattoos, and goes after him. Tim goes skating to relax. A car almost hits him, and he magically puts it in a hole as a response. His scorpion tattoo stabs him painfully in return, as it is supposed to keep him from practicing ill-advised magic.

At home, Bill and his new lady-friend, Holly, her son Cyril, and their housekeeper Gwendolyn are trying to get the house ready for Tim's 14th birthday.

The occupants of the car are now stuck inside, and as they try to get out, they are visited by the man's son, and two mysterious people in black, known as the Margraves. It turns out that the couple in the care are actually having an affair. The boy is understandably unhappy with his father, and under the Margraves' supervision, he magically explodes the car and the couple inside. The explosion also destroys him, but he recreates himself. He is one of a series of children called the Strafenkind that are manipulated by the Margraves.

Tim gets some fabric for Gwendolyn, but while at the store, he sees a miniature statue version of his friend Jimmy, last seen in issue 9 when he was turned into gutta-percha by Reverend Slaggingham. Tim buys him and as he walks away wondering who did it, the wall (another of Tim's childhood creations, known as In the No!) tells him it was Slaggingham. It then tells him that Cyril is eating his cake, and Tim doesn't even know who he is, and that Gwendolyn is leaving.

Cyril, meanwhile, has finished the cake and runs off, no longer happy with his mom now that she's fascinated with Bill. He runs into the Margraves, who tell him how right he is to be angry at Tim, saying that he is too amazing to be true. Then they give him one of their magic pins, and tell him to go home and explode in his mother's presence.

Tim shows up, however, and releases Cyril from their spell, and reveals that the two Margraves are in fact one combined being. Tim thanks them for helping him realize that he can't stay around his family and friends, where he'll always endanger them. The Margrave leaves, and Tim walks off, with Jimmy in his pocket.
name: Red Rover, Red Rover.

description: Lovers Hazel and Foxglove reach a pivotal crossroads in their life and relationship. But when Death becomes involved with several souls dearest to Foxglove, Fox must discover whether her love is strong enough to follow Hazel into Death's realm, and if either of them will return alive.
name: Chapter One: Things You Just Do When You're Bored

volume.name: Death: The Time of Your Life

description: "Future Perfect." Wally has disappeared, but a new, futuristic speedster in a blue costume has come back to this time period. Meanwhile, Chillblaine attacks, and Jesse Quick and others attend Johnny Quick's funeral.
name: Future Perfect

description:
Kyle's quest to become a better hero brings him face-to-face with the Amazing Amazon. Can Green Lantern and Wonder Woman stop a madwoman from destroying Gateway City?

Kyle and Wonder woman do battle, they want it to seem like he’s a villain and he’s killed her. Things play out while a galaxy away the eighteen remaining darkstars prepare to descend on Rann where they will do battle with the would-be world conqueror who has been laying waste to planets. Back on Earth Diana and Kyle’s plan is good and they manage to get some intergalactic criminals out of hiding. Kyle battles the female leader and wonderwoman the rest. Kyle holds back and almost gets them killed and WW saves the day. She gives kyle the final lesson of a hero, don’t hold back when battle is the only choice with that she departs and Kyle gets a visit from Donna after avoiding her since their fight.
name: Hero Quest part 3: Gateway

description: Special anniversary issue! Fallen into a coma, Constantine is transported to the darkest corner of his own personal hell, to an unwilling reunion with his estranged and long-deceased father! With Constantine's adversary, the First of the Fallen, as a gleeful witness, father and son unravel the layers of their stormy relationship and at last confront the dark secret behind their mutual animosity.
name: Sins of the Father

description: Jim Crow and the team mount a magical search for King Mob, who is being broken by Sir Miles and ready to spill the secrets of the Invisibles! At least, that's what he wants Sir Miles to think.
name: Entropy in the U.K., Part Three: Assasin

description:
The vampire Cassidy returns in part 1 of the 4-part ''Hunters,'' as two secret societies converge on Jesse Custer. One is The Grail, a clandestine order dedicated to preserving the world's greatest secret. The other is the Gomorrah People, a cult of carnal extremists led by the depraved Jesus de Sade.

Jesse and Tulip go to San Francisco to meet up with Cassidy; Jesus De Sade, the Lord of the Gomorrah People, plans a party; a conspiracy-within-a-conspiracy is uncovered.
name: Came A Pale Rider (Hunters Part 1)

description:
(continued from Azrael 16)

Tim was cured. Nightwing and Batman went out to clean up some of the mess in their city. Robin went to the aid of the GCPD when he heard they were in a shootout with a local gang while trying to deliver the antidote. Still shaken from his ordeal, Robin took a break on a rooftop. Catwoman found him and gave him a hand taking down the gang-bangers. Tim returned home.
name: Contagion, Part 11: Bitter Dregs

description: With the decade coming to a close and war apparently looming ever closer, two inventors travel to New York to pitch their ideas--one of those inventors being Ted Knight, also known as the Starman!
name: The Mist: Act One of Four
Requiem (The Pilgrimage Of Lucas Hart Part Four)

description: Final issue. Part 3 of the 3-part 'After Kathy.' Together they've suffered through horror, disease, even death. Now in the sanity-straining series finale, Shade and Kathy are reunited at last. But with a past grounded in madness, what sort of future awaits Vertigo's strangest lovers?
name: After Kathy, Part Three: How It All Started

description: While in the Caribbean, the Spectre encounters a ghost ship and learns its captain's horrifying story.
name: Ill Will

description:
It's a tale of "Time Past" as the original Starman confronts his arch-foe, the Mist, during the Golden Age!

Another Tale of Times Past, Ted Knight's first time facing The Mist, as recorded in The Shade's journal.
name: First Joust

description:
When a giant crab beast rises out of the sea, the only thing standing in its way is Hawaii's own dynamic duo--Superboy and Knockout. But who is that plotting and scheming from the shadows?

Superboy is training with Knockout at the ruins of his old school Ilupani High (which was destroyed in a battle from last issue) when members of the school board show up. Superboy starts apologizing as Knockout asks to be left out of it, bailing on Superboy. His old teacher tells him that the board has decided to expel Superboy from public school to "minimize future destruction". We move onto the Police Academy where a Metropolis SCU agent demonstrates a weapon for the newly established Hawaii SCU, on an unsuspecting Roxy Leech (who is now a week into her police training.) It is mentioned the weapon is not even available to the Metro SCU. The squad consisting of the SCU officer, SWAT members, Inspector Makoa and Max Lopaka of homicide (introduced here) are talking about the murder case of an officer who died in last issue's fight, named in this issue as Wes Smithson. This case is the center of the mini series' plot as well as the Hawaii SCU's first case. They are waiting for Dubbilex who would help recreate the scene of the murder using his psychic power.

Meanwhile, as Knockout tells Superboy that he's left with just powers training (which he previously had to split time with real school) a giant robot crab stars attacking the beach. They fight the crab, the crab catches fire and changes into a fire monster, and Superboy realizes it's someone he knows, Bernie Murlock aka B.E.M (from issue 10). Reporter Tana Moon arrives and Superboy wants to settle previous issues between the 2 women, but Knockout has other plans. She kisses Superboy and persuades Superboy to take her and leave the scene leaving Tana in shock to get her story from the rescued B.E.M. Superboy feels bad about leaving without a word to Tana, Knockout tells him he now has to choose between "kindergarten" and "college". By now Dubbilex has pieced the scene of the battle with the furies from the memories of police officers who were present there. Knockout is revealed to be pushing Wes Smithson out, snapping his spine in the process. The SCU recruits the help of Roxy as a consultant in the hunt for Knockout and the skills of Snare of Draper Inc.
name: Losin' It! Part 2 of 6: Strange Bedfellows

description: Comics legend Curt Swan guest-pencils the most off-beat SWAMP THING story of recent years. When lovable hippie Chester Williams forsakes his left-wing past for the ultraconservative life of a New York City cop, the powers that be decide he's just the man to talk the Swamp Thing out of his environmentally-conscious plans for humankind. Is it an imaginary story...or a frightening glimpse of America's future?
name: Chester Williams: American Cop

description: Meet Maggot, a slightly crazy California chick who's obsessed with the Vamps. They want nothing to do with her, but she may prove to be more valuable than they realize. Plus, things heat up as Skeeter teaches Rhys the agony and ecstasy of being a half-vamp.
name: Undeath in Venice

description: Wonder Woman and Morgaine Le Fay meet face-to-face as warriors on a mystical plane, where the prize of their contest could be eternal life for Le Fay…or death for Diana! Featuring appearances by Vandal Savage and General Immortus.
name: Lifelines, Part 4

person_credits.name: Roberta Gregory
person_credits.role: writer, editor, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: The police and the super-heroes all recover from the ended gang war, while The Deadly Duo and a team called Brute Force arrive late to end it. While Chelsea Nirvana, alias the new Doctor Nirvana, and the Inhabitor kill her father, the original Doctor Nirvana, Rapture proposes to the Dragon.

More mafia members are starting to die in strange gruesome ways, and it seems there are no clues to who is commiting the murders.

Meanwhile Spawn is regressing as he suit slowly begins to make decisions for him. He starts bathing in decay, and filth, trying to sponge off any possible evil source

Eventually the creature behind the mafia murders is revealed, and as it turns out its none other than Tremor (See #25).

Tremor persuades Spawn to help him destroy Twist, and find his brother, in return for some vital information.
name: Revenge
Revelations

description: To protect the children of Team 7, Grifter uploads a virus to the I.O. computers to prevent anyone from accessing the personnel files of Team 7.
name: The Fifth Corner Of The World

description:
The Hulk’s arch-nemesis Leader conceives a plan that involves the destruction of world famous landmarks. But by the time the Avengers catch wind of this plot, will it be too late to stop the Leader’s reign of terror?

Hawkeye and the Scarlet Witch are confrronted by the military, meanwhile Hotshot and Jailbait look for Hulk after his brawl with Thor.
name: Crawling from the Wreckage

description:
Cap is exiled for his apparent treasonous acts against the Country he symbolizes.

He now must fight as a criminal and hope he can regain his citizenship once gain.
name: Man Without a Country, Part 1: Executive Action

description: Shinobi Shaw asks Captain Britain to join the London branch of the Hellfire Club, fearing that it is about to go rogue.
name: Fireback

description: The citizens of Freetown figure out the identity of the Alliance Leader. Meanwhile, Thor and Hulk (as Maestro) battle it out to the death in the Tundra..only one of them will survive as the U.S. government takes drastic action
name: Ghosts of the Future, Part 5: The Big Bang

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

name: What if Shard Had Lived Instead of Bishop?

description:
Continued from Cable #30. Nate Grey takes on Exodus, a fight that recharges and sustains the former Acolyte. Cable struggles with the charge of taking Nate out, but he can't make up his mind before Nate dispatches Exodus and turns to take on Cable. Story concludes in Cable #31.

Note: Includes a pin-up of Cable and Nate Grey.
name: Fallen from Grace

description:
Crashing into the Moonguzzit sea sets the would-be rescuers off to a poor start which only turns worse when capture by the Sky Pirates is their only way out.  
 
Captured and restrained they are escorted to the Sky Cove where they are sold as the latest contestants for the coves favorite form of  entertainment ...  the arena!

name: Fire From Heaven Chapter Three of Fourteen

description:
Chaos erupts in Indianapolis! And while the Grendels usually ride chaos like a bronco, this time they find themselves unable to saddle up! Their chief, Hack, has fallen for one of the locals, a nurse named Dana. Problem is, Dana's son is the one creating the chaos; he's picking off Grendels like a madman vigilante. Hack's gotta decide -- is he willing to lose his status as Grendel Chief, or lose the woman he loves?

Includes a black-and-white preview of Batman/Grendel II. James Gordon, Batman, and Grendel Prime only appear in this preview.
name: Book 5

volume.name: Grendel Tales: The Devil May Care

name: Fall of the Tempo, Part One of Two

description:
Aquaman goes to the Dreaming City in the Himalayas to enlist their aid, leading him to a confrontation with their ruler: Ocean Master!

Ocean master struggles with the aftermath of his deal with Nero, when his staff slips from his hand while he sleeps causing him much anguish.While Aquaman and Dolphin continue their journey to the next city while discussing Dolphin's murder of the High Seer and her feelings of love for Aquaman, which Aquaman shrugs off. The two then arrive at Himalayas to find the next lost city (Dreaming City), as admiral Strom as Ocean master reveals his presence having caught Aquaman's grappling hook on his staff sending an energy attack through it. The two then begin a battle until separate by an avalanche with Aquaman abandoning Orm to save a falling Dolphin.

Meanwhile Strom seeing the result of the battle Strom attempts to flee in a ship only to be stopped by a unseen assailant who completely covers him in snow. Aquaman and Dolphin are then met by a couple who ask of their relationship with ocean master and they are invited inside a cave through a holographic wall. Once inside the city, they are incapacitated by Ocean Master who reveals that the Dreaming City is in fact his. He then places them in a torture scenario in which will eventually end in both their deaths.His plan is foiled however when a ship comes flying in, with the pilot being none other then Garth back from his own journey.
name: Brother's Keeper

description: Wolverine, Apocalypse’s Horseman of Death? He may regain his Adamantium, but will Logan lose his mind? And what does the fruition of Genesis’ plan mean for the Dark Riders and Cyber? The return of feral Wolverine!
name: Furnace Of His Brain, Anvil Of His Heart

description:
Cable finds Nate Grey and offers to help the misguided young man. Nate is able to scan Cable's mind and sees enemies. Instead of accepting the help, Nate Grey obliterates the surroundings, only to be confronted by Exodus. Story continues in X-Man #14.

Note: Includes a brief, three-page history of Cable.
name: For Every Action...

description: The Avengers inadvertently stumble upon the wedding of Titania and Absorbing Man. They proceed to battle with the various villains who are attending.
name: The Old Ball and Chain
A Force of One

description: Piece by piece, inch by inch . . . nothing big is ever built overnight. A clue here, a memory there. . . that's all X has had in his search to discover who he is and where he's come from. But now, after more than two years, it all makes sense. Now, as he lay near death at the hands of Coffin, it all comes back to him. The pieces are in place and the puzzle is complete in this issue of X!
name: Final Hand!

description: Luse and the other assassins are sitting around telling war stories as Morachi and Talon decide to ask Luse if he knows where Lester is. Then it gets dark?
name: Five: Ascending Notorious

description: Unexpected betrayals and intimate revelations about da Vinci and his beloved Salai mark the final chapter of Leonardo's life.

[continued from Batman 529]
Poison Ivy continued selling the antidote to the highest bidders inside Babylon Towers. Batman went in after her. Huntress and Nightwing realized Robin had been infected. Gordon met Batman inside looking for Ivy. The antidote failed.
[continued in Detective 629
name: Falls Upon Angel of Death: Contagion: Part Seven
Road Trip! Part 1 - There is No Sun in Gotham

description: Jeb takes a bullet from the mob to save Lois Lane.
name: The Heat Is On!

description:
In the looming shadow of the total destruction of the universe, the deadliest villains in the cosmos--the Fatal Five--set out to utterly crush the Legion.

The Legion of Super-Heroes is locked on Takron-Galtos, alone with the Fatal Five after learning the Sun-Eater story was all a hoax. Despite having twice the Five's numbers, the Legion is quickly taken down.
name: Fatal Fight!

description:
Tremor and Spawn make their way to Twists mansion.

Tremor takes a more hidden route, while spawn takes a direct path, and fends off Twist's gaurds.

Finally Tremor has his oppurtunity to interogate Twist, when suddenly he is shot at by his own brother! Who apparently has been a Mafia henchmen ever since his family died.

Tremor tries to convince his brother david that he is still his brother, however David still believes that his brother had died with the rest of the family. Suddenly Spawn shows up, and badly beats up David, unfortunately angering Tremor.

It is after this that Tremor takes his weakened brother out of the Twist Mansion, in order to get him some medical help.

Spawn however does what he does best, and threatens Twist with yet another file he's found, afterwards he tells him to back off the fitzgerald family.
name: Twisted

description:
Kitten, Maribel, and Gaby are three very different girls with one single purpose -- break their pal Una out of her Tijuana prison cell! With the super-powered guards pulling overtime, that's no easy feat. But if the job can be pulled off, this is the trio that'll do it. Kitten can crush the most fearsome robots with her atomic eyebeams; Maribel is the queen of the savage Hollywood jungles; and Gaby . . . well, not even a 1950 Caddy can bowl over Gaby. So it's off to Tijuana in Gilbert Hernandez's Girl Crazy.

Multiple Stories in this Issue:

"What's Knitten' Kitten?"

"Maribel of Hollywood"

"Gaby, Gaby, Hey"

Masterless, mercenary, hell-bent on destruction -- that's Queenie for you, always living in the moment! And living in the moment is about all she can hope for when Biovoc sends the clone-killer Rusk to bring her in. Biovoc wants to start exploiting a stolen genetic "virus" without interference from Queenie and company. Rusk wants revenge on Queenie and her sister clone, Vector. Queenie wants to stay alive just long enough to thwart Biovoc and enjoy her newfound romance for a while . . . yes, romance!

"Strange Visitor" kicks off what is arguably the greatest Elseworlds tale ever told. Kingdom Come, replete with grand storytelling and biblical prophecy, takes place in the near future when Superman has retired and a new, ruthlessly violent generation of "heroes" has corrupted the Earth, their questionable deeds culminating in the destruction of Kansas.
name: Strange Visitor

description: While on a case with Andy in the present time, Turok flashbacks and recalls his younger days in his tribe when he sought to win the hand in marriage of Ravenwing, the chief's daughter.
name: Son Of Stone

description:
Overview
The water in Puget Sound is pretty opaque -- a good thing for Concrete, who was forced to dive in to avoid a bunch of irate loggers. He's in Canada illegally traveling with a pack of Earth First!ers, and if he's seen he could be connected to those left-wing environmentalists and the property destruction they've caused. But that was the problem that caused him to jump. Now his problem is getting out of the Sound, finding the First!ers, and making his way back to America -- unseen.

New York is a young man's best friend -- if that young man has a steady job that pays big bucks. But to comic-book artist Al Milgrom, fresh off the bus from the Midwest, The Big Apple is the worst kind of enemy. He has no job and no friends. But what he does have is his "New York Pets"! Join Al Milgrom -- one of the shapers of the Silver Age of comics -- in this behind-the-scenes look at the creation of a cartoonist. Plus the twists and dips keep on coming in Paul Pope's "One Trick Rip-Off"; Renée French continues to surprise us in "The Ninth Gland"; and the culinary wonders of the underworld are revealed in Jack Pollock's "Devil Chef"!

OverviewThe first of a two-part Hellboy crossover! Word at the Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense says there's a ghost in Arcadia. A ghost that hunts. A ghost that kills people. Not the kind that pushes you down a flight of stairs or grabs the wheel when you're driving -- the kind that cuts you in half with a pair of .45 automatics. If she's a ghost -- a "real" ghost -- then she's one of a kind, and the Bureau wants her. And if anyone can get her, you can bet it's Hellboy . . .

first_appearance_teams.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

team_credits.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

description: It was dedication that got Hartigan put away -- his dedication to saving a little girl, and a corrupt politician's dedication to saving himself. But now Hartigan's done his time and paid his debt for all the crimes he didn't commit. Once again he's a free man. Free to uncover the fate of that little girl, whose loyalty kept him sane all those years. Free to find out why her letters mysteriously and disturbingly ceased arriving just months before his release. And free to do whatever it takes to save that little girl . . . again.

person_credits.name: Frank Miller
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, cover

description: An innocent Noodles has been captured by the corrupt police force, and there's nothing Usagi can do -- except expose his persecutors' deceptions. Policeman Yoriki Matsuda is a puppet of the local criminals, but once the puppet is eliminated, the puppet masters fall as well.
name: Noodles, Part 2

person_credits.name: Stan Sakai
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description:
When Azrael comes dangerously close to killing a former foe, Jean-Paul believes he's become a threat to both himself and his friends. Brian Bryan suggests a radical therapist, Doctor Orchid. But the good doctor may use the Angel of Vengeance for his own purposes.

Jean Paul and Lilhy were attacked the the two men who'd previously kidnapped Shondra Kinsolving. Jean Paul took them down and got Lilhy to a hospital - she'd received a flesh wound from a gunshot. Brian sent Jean Paul to the tropics to see Dr. Orchid, a former associate.
name: Angel in Flames Part One: A Distant Savior

description: Batman took down a pawn shop owner and three possible buyers of stolen Incan treasure. One of the men shot the back of his head off. Deadman - Boston Brand - possessed one of the men who was later killed outside. He was working on the case of the stolen artifacts. In the dead guy's body, Brand talked to Batman. They set off for Peru after finding a map.
name: The Deadman Connection, Part 1: Sweat of the Sun, Tears of the Moon

description:
When a local tabloid reports that Batman has fired Robin, the streets and rooftops of Gotham City become crowded with costumed would-be sidekicks auditioning for the job. And when one of the "Robins" is kidnapped, Batman and the real Robin's lives are the ransom.

When the citizens of Gotham find out that Robin has quit, citizens start dressing up like Robin, trying to become the new Boy Wonder.
name: Round Robin

description: Batman, with an assist from Jim Gordon, stops both the serial murderer known as the Circuit Killer and the vigilante who has been shooting criminals while wearing a bat mask, part three of three.
name: Idols Part 3 of 3

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description:
Molly is staying with her grandmother in Ireland, after returning from Hell. They have a special relationship, as her gran shares her occasional magical sense of the world. Gran gives her a letter about Tim, which felt dangerous to her, and she asks Molly to read it on top of a reputedly magical hill.

Molly agrees and rides off. When they get there, the horse starts to eat the letter. Although it's torn, she manages to read most of it. It's from Gwendolyn, and relates the after-effects of the previous issue: Tim returned home and got into a row wth his dad about Cyril. Gwen tried to convince him to stay home, but he left in secret in the morning, leaving a note asking her to relate his love to Molly. Gwen also plans to leave. Molly realizes that Tim heard what she said about him and his future self when she was with Marya.

Molly resolves to find Tim and patch up their problems. Knowing the magic of the hill, she hopes to get the aid of the local fairies in finding Tim. However, the Amadan was already watching her, and flies down. She recognizes him from when she met Auberon, and he introduces himself as a fool. She laughs, at which he is angered, but she says she is the greater fool. He challenges her to a contest of who is the greater fool, and will grant her her desire if she wins. The other giant rocks on the hill are proof of what happens to losers. The Amadan flies off to prepare, and one of the stones gives her advice as she waits: follow her heart while in faerie.

(Gwendolyn ["Sister Staylace"] only appears through her writing in the note.)
name: And Sure in Language Strange She Said

description: You're Foxglove, a rich and famous rock star: and today, your manager died, your girlfriend disappeared and you learn you were about to get outed as a lesbian by a glossy magazine. And if you're going to survive, you're going to have to journey into the realm of Death.
name: Chapter Two: Imaginary Solutions

volume.name: Death: The Time of Your Life

description: The 'Wonder Twins', escaped slaves of an alien warlord, officially join the team.
name: --So Now What Do We Do?

description: "Race Against Time! - Chapter One: Wally World." This issue finds Wally West in the 64th century, where he is worshipped as a god. Meanwhile, John (the blue-clad speedster from the future) and Linda Park go after Chillblaine and Golden Glider.
name: Race Against Time Part 1

description: John's affinity with the supernatural spoils a soccer game when a demon that thrives on holloganism shows up. Naturally, the demon takes the time to torment John. And a certain soccer fan...
name: Football: It's A Funny Old Game
